#!ipxe
# bty PXE bootstrap - fetched by iPXE clients on second-stage DHCP.
# Chains to the per-MAC plan endpoint on the same host that served
# this script (Host header), so the URL stays correct regardless of
# whether the operator addresses the server by IP, hostname, or
# .local mDNS name.
#
# ``${mac:hexhyp}`` (no NIC prefix) is iPXE's MAC of the *current*
# network device -- the one that just succeeded DHCP and fetched
# this script. NEVER hardcode ``${net0/mac:hexhyp}`` here: on a
# multi-NIC box where net0 is link-down (a common shape -- onboard
# NIC unplugged, USB or expansion-card NIC actually connected),
# iPXE still reads net0's MAC from the NIC's EEPROM and would
# query bty with the wrong MAC. bty would then correctly answer
# "no assignment for <inactive NIC's MAC>" and the chain fails.
chain http://{{ host }}/pxe/${mac:hexhyp}
